In [ ]:
def convert (col):
    if col=='No Stress':
        return 1
    elif col=='Little':
        return 2
    elif col=='Bad':
        return 3
    else:
        return 4
stress = behavior.copy()
stress['Stress Level '] = stress['Stress Level '].apply(convert)
stress['Stress Level '].value_counts()

machine_learning = behavior[['10th Mark','college mark']]
train_set, test_set = train_test_split(machine_learning, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)

X_train = train_set.drop(['college mark'], axis=1)
y_train = train_set[['college mark']]
X_test = test_set.drop(['college mark'],axis=1)
y_test = test_set[['college mark']]

model = LinearRegression()
model.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
error_value = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred, squared=False)
print(error_value)

Q3: Does higher daily studying time correlate with higher salary expectations¶

Analytical¶

In [ ]:
student = pd.read_csv('Student_Behaviour.csv')
In [ ]:
# grab the last two digits on the daily studing time column
student['daily_studying_time'] = student['daily studing time'].str.split(' ').str[-2]
# change the daily studying time column to int type
student['daily_studying_time'] = student['daily_studying_time'].astype(int)
In [ ]:
def convert_to_minutes(time):
    if len(str(time)) == 1:
        return time * 60
    else:
        return time
    
student['daily_studying_time'] = student['daily_studying_time'].apply(convert_to_minutes)
student.head(5)
